args: Odd. I've been searching for quite some\ntime, but I still haven't found the girl...
(It all started a few days ago. We were\nplaying hide-and-seek, and in the middle\nof the game, she vanished.)

(She hasn't gone home, and no one's
heard from her. I leveraged my cuteness
to gather information from the townsfolk,
but nobody's seen hide nor hair of her.)
I can't believe I haven't turned up a\nsingle lead! What the heck is going on?
But come to think of it, there HAVE been\na lot of disappearances in Hinomoto\nlately... Could this be connected?
Vice?! What are you doing here?\nAnd why the fruit analogy?
You're normally so carefree, so when\nI saw you poking around, all serious,\nI wondered what was going on.
That's why I took it upon myself to\ninvestigate what happened with that kid.
Really?! Well, did you turn anything up?
Easy. Info's not going anywhere.\nI heard a fishy little rumor via\nmy intelligence network.
Apparently, a notorious band of thieves has\nmoved in on this town, and is plying their\ncriminal trade.
Yet there hasn't been a single eyewitness\nto their misdeeds. I bet they're cleaning\nhouse.
Surely you don't mean that they're\nbeing silenced—or worse?!
This is all speculation. But it would\nbe worthwhile to investigate.
I've marked a few places on this map\nwhere their hideout might be, so we'll\ngo together and—
Thanks, Vice! I'm gonna take point!
Hey, stop! You didn't even let me finish\ntalking! You can't go alone, it's gonna be\ndangerou—dammit, he's already gone!
No luck so far. This is the last place.
My mind is racing with all the awful things\nthat could be happening to her right now.\nPlease be safe, please be safe...!
Hmph. Irritatin' kid, snoopin' around.\nTime for you to go beddy-bye. Forever.
I'm in...the Halidom? I'm guessing I\nscrewed up and you came to the rescue.
You guessed right. Gee, if only someone\nhad warned you not to take off running\nwhile he was in the middle of talking.
...I'm sorry, Vice. You're right. I goofed.
Listen, Chitose. I want you to forget about\nthis whole matter.
What?! You want me to just leave that girl\nto die?!
Never said that. But I'm gonna be the one\nto help her. The people we're up against...\nthey're bad news.
This band of thieves is notorious.\nThe worst of 'em would slit your\nthroat the moment they saw you.
In other words, they're pros. All the\ncuteness in the world won't get you\nanywhere with guys like them.
So do me a favor and leave this to me.
I said, ＂not happening.＂ I made that girl a\npromise: that no matter what woes she\nmight have, I'd help her solve them.
I don't want to betray her—or myself.\nI'm going to figure this out my own way.
Cuteness is my reason for being.\nIt's my strength. And sometimes,\nI think it might be my weakness, too.

Yet as a paragon of all things adorable,
I believe in cuteness more than anyone. 
That's why no matter what, I will use it
to challenge any problem head-on!
An admirable sentiment. But how are\nyou going to make this work? You know,\nconcretely?
Ah, you're awake, Chitose.\nYou have guests.
Fans of yours who live in the area.\nScores of them. They say they'd like\nto help you in your time of need.
See, I told you cuteness could solve\nanything! Let's go, Vice!
Go where? What are we doing?!
Isn't it obvious?! I'm gonna save that\ngirl the way only I know how! *wink*
